# Redemption Rule Management

**Route:** `redemption-rules` · **Arch phase:** 1 · See `ARCHITECTURE.md` §4

## Purpose

Configure and review point-redemption rules. Same UX as earning rules with redemption-specific fields. Shares Rule Engine with `ruleMode: "REDEEM"` via `RuleModule`.

**Note:** `PointConfig` (Tab General) lives under Earning Rule route only — redemption route has Rule tab only.

## Key UI (beyond earning rules)

- Extra table column: Cap type (`rule.redemption.capType`)
- Drawer fields: Cap type, value point %, value min, value max

**Cap types:** `cashback`, `discount`, `bill_payment`, `donasi`, `point_pihak_ketiga`, `kupon_undian`, `voucher`, `e_wallet`, `lelang`, `barang`, `annual_fee`

**Open question:** `ruleTabId` and `sourceTypeId` on redemption mock data — Gap #4 in ARCHITECTURE.md §9.

## User flow

Same as earning rules (employee + approver). Redemption drawer fields when `ruleMode === "REDEEM"`. See `prd-rule-drawer` for drawer detail.

## Permissions

Identical to earning rules (`canEdit` in `src/domain/ruleStatus.ts`).

## State & data

Same as `RuleModule` with `ruleMode: "REDEEM"`. Data: `getRulesByMode("REDEEM")`, type `Rule` with optional `redemption: RedemptionHeader`.

Mock: 5 redemption rules in `rules[]`.

## Status

Same as earning Rule tab — list, drawer, role-gated edit done (UI); submit/save, inactive toggle, export non-functional.
